JDK 5.0? It Is Realy JDK 1.5 Because The Changes And New Features are so significant that a shift from 1.4 to 1.5 just didnt seem to express the magnitude of the change. instead, sun elected to increase the version number to 5 as a way of emphasizing that a major event was taking place.

                     Basicaly 5 is the external version number and 1.5 is the internal version number....
